Pilots don't do brain surgery because they have no idea what they are doing! Likewise, brain surgeons don't typically sit around and talk about how to fly a plane.  I wouldn't trust a baker to design architecturally sound house.  Garbage men who have never studied rocket science don't sit around and talk about it.  This is also why dog groomers don't cut peoples hair, fishermen don't tame lions, strippers don't fight fires, Stephen Spielberg will never find the cure for AIDS, Michael Jordan doesn't play for the NFL, Martha Stewart doesn't ride a motorcycle, Paris hilton won't run for president, and I'm not a famous fucking band member, the captain of a ship, or an adult film producer!!!!.............Why?  Because these people don't know the first thing about any of this!  The point is, don't take advice from fat people on how to do sit ups! Ok, that's not really the point...  I've been here in Boston for a very short while.  Some how people are already making serious misjudgments about me.


So why do people insist on talking about what they think people should and shouldn't do, without knowing the first thing about them?  When you can write at least 3 pages, front and back, in detail about me, then (AND ONLY THEN) I'll give a fuck about what you have to say.
Until then, I could give a fuck less.


people are the fucking PLAGUE

I continue to change and evolve every single day!!!  I haven't looked back on myself since I looked back at my senior year.  Now I think back to six months ago: I had to be a completely different person than I am now.  It's not a bad thing.  I'm just getting older, experiencing more, and becoming(of all things!) smarter!  I can see some things remaining consistant in me. I guess those things will eventually define me.
Everything that seemed important months ago is long gone and meaningless.  
It just shows me that EVERYthing will get better in time, and if it doesn't, it will just fade out and become meaningless anyways.  I hope everything that I hate about myself fades into my past as well.  Time is the strangest thing.

:::Thinking about a comment made today.  It reproves to me a well known fact.  Over and over I tell myself that if I get involved with people too quickly I'll end up hurt, and over and over I take it too far too fast.  When will I learn?  Don't I deserve more?  Every relationship I've ever been involved in was pointless.  I have been nothing but a fling for every person I get close to with the exception of one.  

The  trouble is not meeting nice guys.  I've meet tons! The problem is that I don't act like a 'nice girl' around them.  I can't control what I do.  Or I don't control what I do.

I'm not feeling to good about myself lately. 
I guess I'm just as bad as any horny guy.
